Manx: Yn Caslys shoh Jeh Lhong-Raue Viking, yn Shenn Cowrey-Eillagh Jeh Ellan Vannin va Chebbit Liorish y Sleigh Manningh Gys H.H.H. yn Princess Victoria Moirrey, Ec y Traa Jeh’n Phoose Ec[1] Rish H.R.H. yn Duic Jeh yn Shiagtoo Vee, 1893.[2]
English: This model of a Viking galley, the ancient arms of the Isle of Man, was presented by the Manx people to H.R.H. the Princess Victoria Mary, on the occasion of her marriage with H.R.H. the Duke of York. July 6. 1893.
Notes:
[1] ec] eck
[2] Some words are missing here, after ‘Duic’ the Manx for ‘of York’ is missing, as is the Manx for ‘the sixth day’.
